(541, NULL, 11, 55, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Mustard Gold Tussar Silk Hand Embroidery Kantha Stitch Saree', 'I-000133', 'productImages/AWS8L1714632764.png', '[\"17146327642Tomu.png\",\"1714632764j57yw.png\",\"1714632765saQzu.png\"]', 'Indulge in elegance with this exquisite Mustard Gold Tussar Silk Hand Embroidery Kantha Stitch Saree. Crafted with the finest Tussar silk, its rich mustard gold hue exudes sophistication. Adorned with intricate hand embroidery in Kantha stitch, this saree is a testament to traditional craftsmanship and timeless beauty. Perfect for special occasions or cultural festivities, it promises to elevate your style with its graceful charm and artisanal allure.', '<p><strong>Material</strong>: Tussar Silk</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Color</strong>: Mustard Gold</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Embroidery Technique</strong>: Hand Embroidery Kantha Stitch</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Description</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Elevate your ethnic wardrobe with this exquisite Mustard Gold Tussar Silk Saree adorned with intricate hand embroidery in Kantha stitch. Tussar silk, also known as &#39;Kosa Silk&#39;, is renowned for its rich texture and natural gold hue, adding a touch of sophistication to any ensemble.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The mustard gold base of this saree exudes warmth and elegance, making it a perfect choice for both daytime events and evening soir&eacute;es. The soft sheen of the silk fabric lends a luxurious appeal, while the intricate hand embroidery in Kantha stitch adds an artisanal touch, showcasing the skilled craftsmanship of Indian artisans.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Kantha stitch, originating from the Bengal region&nbsp;is characterized by its fine, running stitch that creates beautiful motifs and patterns. Each motif on this saree tells a story, reflecting the rich cultural heritage of India. The hand embroidery adds depth and dimension to the saree, enhancing its visual appeal and making it a statement piece for any occasion.</p>', NULL, NULL, 4500, 0, 0, 1, 1, 'Saree,Traditional Saree', NULL, NULL, 'saree-1714632764QXB52', 8, 0, NULL, 'Mustard Gold Tussar Silk Hand Embroidery Kantha Stitch Saree', 'Saree ,Traditional Saree', 'Pair it with traditional gold jewelry and a sleek blouse to complete the look, or experiment with contemporary styles for a modern twist.', 1, 0, 0, '2024-05-02 04:52:44', '2024-06-01 02:41:21'),
(542, NULL, 11, 55, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'White Kantha Stitch Saree Blended Silk Saree', 'I-000133', 'productImages/giFUN1714633987.png', '[\"1714633987saUBb.png\",\"1714633987TGRAv.png\",\"1714633987qWnv8.png\",\"1714633988HSD0M.png\"]', 'The White Kantha Stitch Saree is a stunning piece crafted from blended silk, known for its luxurious texture and elegant drape. This saree features intricate Kantha stitch embroidery, a traditional form of running stitch originating from Bengal. The white base lends a timeless appeal, while the Kantha stitch adds intricate detailing and a touch of cultural heritage to the ensemble. Perfect for special occasions or cultural celebrations, this saree effortlessly combines tradition with contemporary style.', '<p>The White Kantha Stitch Blended Silk Saree is a stunning piece of traditional&nbsp;attire that beautifully combines the elegance of silk with the intricate artistry of Kantha stitching. Here&#39;s a full description:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Material:</strong> Blended Silk - This saree is crafted from a luxurious blend of silk fabric, which offers a smooth texture and a subtle sheen, enhancing its overall appeal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Color:</strong> White - The saree features a pristine white hue, exuding purity, grace, and timeless charm. White is a versatile color that complements various skin tones and can be adorned for a multitude of occasions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Design:</strong> Kantha Stitch - The defining feature of this saree is the exquisite Kantha stitching embellishment. Kantha is a traditional form of embroidery originating from the Indian subcontinent, particularly popular in the Bengal region. It involves intricate hand-stitching in beautiful patterns, often depicting motifs inspired by nature, folklore, or geometric designs. The Kantha stitching on this saree adds depth, texture, and a touch of artisanal elegance, making it a true work of art.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Border:</strong> The saree is adorned with a delicate border that enhances its overall appeal. The border may feature additional embroidery, embellishments, or contrasting colors to add visual interest and elevate the saree&#39;s aesthetic.</p>', NULL, NULL, 4500, 0, 0, 1, 1, 'Saree,Traditional Saree', NULL, NULL, 'saree-17146339870t3Je', 8, 0, NULL, 'White Kantha Stitch Saree Blended Silk Saree', 'Saree ,Traditional Saree', 'The White Kantha Stitch Blended Silk Saree is a timeless masterpiece that seamlessly blends tradition with contemporary elegance, making it a must-have addition to any discerning fashion enthusiast\'s wardrobe.', 1, 0, 0, '2024-05-02 05:13:07', '2024-05-30 02:44:40'),
(543, NULL, 11, 55, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Coquelicot Orange Tussar Silk Hand Embroidery Kantha Stitch Saree', 'I-000133', 'productImages/qPADI1714634566.jpg', '[\"17146345665bY65.jpg\",\"1714634566M6rth.jpg\",\"171463456660c2s.jpg\",\"17146345666oWLb.jpg\"]', 'The Coquelicot Orange Tussar Silk Hand Embroidery Kantha Stitch Saree is a stunning piece of traditional Indian attire. Crafted from luxurious Tussar silk, known for its rich texture and natural sheen, this saree features intricate hand embroidery in vibrant coquelicot orange hues. The Kantha stitch, a popular embroidery technique originating from West Bengal, adds exquisite detailing and texture to the saree, creating a mesmerizing visual appeal. Perfect for special occasions or cultural events, this saree effortlessly combines elegance with tradition, making it a timeless addition to any wardrobe.', '<p>The Coquelicot Orange Tussar Silk Hand Embroidery Kantha Stitch Saree is a stunning piece of traditional Indian attire that embodies elegance and craftsmanship. Let&#39;s break down its description:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Material</strong>: Tussar Silk - Tussar silk, also known as &#39;Kosa silk,&#39; is valued for its rich texture, natural gold sheen, and durability. It&#39;s obtained from silk-producing worms mainly found in the forests of Jharkhand, Bihar, and West Bengal in India.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Color</strong>: Coquelicot Orange - Coquelicot orange is a vibrant hue reminiscent of the intense color of poppy flowers. It exudes warmth and vitality, making it a perfect choice for celebratory occasions.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Embroidery</strong>: Hand Embroidery - Hand embroidery adds a touch of artistry and individuality to each saree. Skilled artisans meticulously stitch intricate patterns and motifs onto the fabric using needle and thread, resulting in unique and exquisite designs.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Stitching Technique</strong>: Kantha 