(544, NULL, 11, 55, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Pure Yellow Hand Embroidery Kantha Stitch Saree', 'I-000133', 'productImages/jfPNy1714635040.jpg', '[\"17146350407cPko.jpg\",\"17146350401473h.jpg\",\"1714635040bPnEA.jpg\",\"1714635040dwvx4.jpg\"]', 'Elevate your elegance with this radiant yellow saree adorned with exquisite hand embroidery in the traditional Kantha stitch technique. Crafted with precision and passion, each thread narrates a story of skilled craftsmanship and timeless beauty. The vibrant hue of yellow symbolizes joy and optimism, making it perfect for festive occasions or celebrations. Gracefully draping your silhouette, this saree merges tradition with contemporary allure, making it a cherished addition to any wardrobe. Flaunt your individuality with this masterpiece of artistry, and let its charm mesmerize the beholder.', '<p>The Pure Yellow Hand Embroidery Kantha Stitch Saree is a stunning piece of traditional Indian attire that combines elegance with intricate craftsmanship. Here&#39;s a full description of this beautiful saree:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Material</strong>: The saree is made from high-quality, pure yellow fabric, typically silk or cotton, chosen for its smooth texture and luxurious feel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Color</strong>: The saree is dyed in a vibrant shade of yellow, exuding brightness and warmth.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Embroidery Technique</strong>: The saree is adorned with exquisite hand embroidery using the Kantha stitch technique. Kantha is a traditional form of embroidery originating from the Indian subcontinent, particularly Bengal. It involves simple running stitches done by hand in various patterns, often depicting motifs inspired by nature, mythology, or everyday life.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Design</strong>: The design of the saree showcases intricate Kantha embroidery spread across the entire length of the fabric. The motifs and patterns may vary, ranging from floral designs to geometric shapes, depending on the artisan&#39;s creativity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Border</strong>: The saree may feature a contrasting or complementary border, enhancing its visual appeal. The border may also be embellished with additional embroidery or decorative elements.</p>', NULL, NULL, 4500, 0, 0, 1, 1, 'Saree,Traditional Saree', NULL, NULL, 'saree-1714635040bPFgU', 8, 0, NULL, 'Pure Yellow Hand Embroidery Kantha Stitch Saree', 'Saree ,Traditional Saree', 'This saree is suitable for various occasions, including weddings, festivals, formal events, and cultural celebrations. Its vibrant color and intricate embroidery make it a standout choice for special gatherings where traditional attire is preferred.', 1, 0, 0, '2024-05-02 05:30:40', '2024-06-01 02:40:55'),
(545, NULL, 11, 55, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Blue Tussar Silk Hand Embroidery Kantha Stitch Saree', 'I-000133', 'productImages/iccV71714635708.jpg', '[\"1714635708VCcJB.jpg\",\"17146357087EQDt.jpg\",\"1714635708V2F0Z.jpg\",\"1714635708mqfxH.jpg\"]', 'The Tussar Silk Hand Embroidery Kantha Stitch Saree is a luxurious and elegant garment that combines the richness of Tussar silk with the intricate beauty of Kantha embroidery. Crafted by skilled artisans, this saree features delicate hand embroidery using the traditional Kantha stitch, which adds a unique texture and charm to the fabric. Tussar silk, known for its natural sheen and soft texture, lends a luxurious feel to the saree, making it perfect for special occasions and celebrations.', '<p>Tussar silk, known for its rich texture and natural golden sheen, is a luxurious fabric originating from India. Hand embroidery, particularly Kantha stitch, adds an exquisite touch to this already elegant material.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Fabric</strong>: Tussar silk, also known as Kosa silk, is produced from silk worms mainly found in the forests of Jharkhand state in India. It&#39;s characterized by its texture, which is more textured and coarser than other types of silk, giving it a unique appeal. Tussar silk is favored for its natural golden hue and rich feel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Hand Embroidery</strong>: The saree features intricate hand embroidery, specifically employing the Kantha stitch. Kantha is a traditional embroidery style from the Indian subcontinent, particularly prevalent in West Bengal and Bangladesh. It involves simple running stitches along the fabric, often in decorative patterns or motifs. Kantha embroidery is known for its rustic charm and the skilled craftsmanship involved.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Design</strong>: The design of the saree is likely to showcase a blend of traditional and contemporary motifs. It may feature floral patterns, geometric designs, or even narrative themes, all meticulously stitched onto t